rComments: I've got alot of problems with you peoples, and your gonna hear about it.

The class was incredibly difficult, requiring several all-nighters.  Franks worked his students like a slave driver, many times using a whip he called "Old Cracky" on us during exams.  If I could I would hate that old man, but he's just too damn sexy.

Incredible amount of homework, but you'll know the material very well by the end of the semester. Frizanks is very stubborn, so don't even try correcting one of his mistakes. He invented the right-hand rule. Gives directions to other buildings on campus in i-hat and j-hat form.

This is the best professor I have ever encountered here at the University of Illinois.  It is amazing that he has accomplished so much at such a young age.  The funniest thing is that he writes in only capital letters.  I guess he can do whatever he wants as he graduated from MIT in under 3 years.
